<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="105" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
In the phylogenetic analyses, both isolates of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. fibrosae" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" rank="species" species="fibrosae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">C. fibrosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. formed a monophyletic clade, but the sister taxon differed between datasets. These sibling species were either 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. boothii" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" rank="species" species="boothii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">C. boothii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ITS) or 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. pulveracea" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" rank="species" species="pulveracea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">C. pulveracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(LSU and concatenated). Both of these sibling species were described, based on their sexual state and chlamydospores (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(73)80105-6" author="Manoharachary, C" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the British Mycological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" pagination="196 - 198" refId="B21" refString="Manoharachary, C, Ramarao, P, 1973. Thielavia boothii sp. nov. from pond mud. Transactions of the British Mycological Society 61: 196 - 198, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(73)80105-6" title="Thielavia boothii sp. nov. from pond mud." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(73)80105-6" volume="61" year="1973">Manoharachary and Ramarao 1973</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0953756298007564" author="Romero, AI" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" pagination="689 - 695" refId="B32" refString="Romero, AI, Carmaran, CC, Lorenzo, LE, 1999. A new species of Coniochaeta with a key to the species known in Argentina. Mycological Research 103: 689 - 695, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1017/S0953756298007564" title="A new species of Coniochaeta with a key to the species known in Argentina." url="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0953756298007564" volume="103" year="1999">Romero et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.mycres.2006.07.007" author="Garcia, D" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" pagination="1271 - 1289" refId="B11" refString="Garcia, D, Stchigel, AM, Cano, J, Calduch, M, Hawksworth, DL, Guarro, J, 2006. Molecular phylogeny of Coniochaetales. Mycological Research 110: 1271 - 1289, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.mycres.2006.07.007" title="Molecular phylogeny of Coniochaetales." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.mycres.2006.07.007" volume="110" year="2006">
<normalizedToken originalValue="García">Garcia</normalizedToken>
et al. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
). However, we did not find sexual reproductive structures in our species. As a result, we were unable to compare the morphology of these species.
</paragraph>
